{
  "texts": [
    "However, there is a gap between the item representation in LLMs and recommendation, so the indexing of items between LLMs and recommender systems becomes the key and difficult point of LLM-RS.",
    "There are three typical ways to index items: 1) token-based identifiers, 2) description-based identifiers and 3) hybrid identifiers [139,186].",
    "For token-based identifiers, researchers often use numerical IDs to identify items [32].",
    "Since token-based identifiers are widely utilized in traditional recommendation model, they are naturally treated as an itemindexing way for aligning LLMs with recommendation tasks.",
    "For description-based identifiers, researchers generally use the title or other textual attributes of the item as an identifier, and formalize it into natural language as input [3,17,86]."
  ]
}